FBIS4-8495 "dreeu072_y_94011" FBIS-EEU-94-072 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 YUGOSLAVIA Serbia Peace Initiative Discussed Peace Initiative Discussed LD1304184894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 1824 GMT 13 Apr 94 LD1304184894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] Belgrade, 13 Apr (TANJUG) -- Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic this evening again received Vitaliy Churkin, Russian President Boris Yeltsin's special envoy, who arrived in Belgrade following talks in Sarajevo and Pale. As the Serbian president's office has announced, the talks focused on the current situation, while particular attention was paid to the initiative for reaching a general agreement on the cessation of all hostilities on the territory of former Bosnia-Herzegovina. The Serbian president stressed in talks that abandoning the practice of discriminating between the warring sides in former Bosnia-Herzegovina represents an unavoidable precondition for reaching a final peace.
